name: Care-A-Van Pacific Islander
notes: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose, Pfizer 1st/2nd dose Clinic and is by appointment or walk in.  Please note: Pfizer has been authorized for ages 12 – 17 with parental authorization. Johnson & Johnson is authorized for patients over the age of 18. This clinic is located in Vancouver, WA in partnership with Pacific Islander Community Association of WA, WA Department of Health and Bird's Eye Medical. This is a walk-up location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill.  It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are still required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH - COVID Vaccine Site

address.street1: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH: 16327 Ash Way

notes:
**THIS IS A 2ND DOSE PFIZER CLINIC ONLY**
Starting May 13, 2021, everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, you must be 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine. Any minors receiving the vaccine will need a parent or guardian *physically present* to sign the consent form. 

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
